    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-21T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-21T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 21, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Last paragraph Department’s 68, July 20, 7 p.m. No reference was made to the
                    Chilean Government in last paragraph my 101, July 19, 1 p.m. In first sentence
                    last paragraph my 101 the word Bolivia inadvertently omitted. Phrase should read
                    “all American public opinion on Bolivia;”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
